'''Beaglehole Glacier''' ({{Coord|66|33|S|64|7|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] between [[Spur Point]] and [[Friederichsen Glacier]] on the east coast of [[Graham Land]]. It was named by the [[UK Antarctic Place-Names Committee]] after [[John Cawte Beaglehole]], [[New Zealand]] historian of the Antarctic and biographer of Captain [[James Cook]].
