'''Brøgger Glacier''' ({{Coord|54|32|S|36|26|W|type:glacier_source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] {{convert|7|nmi|km}} long, flowing west into the southern part of [[Undine South Harbour]] on the south coast of [[South Georgia Island|South Georgia]]. The name appears on a chart by Professor [[Olaf Holtedahl]], [[Norwegians|Norwegian]] [[geologist]] who investigated South Georgia in 1928, and is probably for Professor [[Waldemar Christofer Brøgger (geologist)|Waldemar Brøgger]], a Norwegian geologist and [[Mineralogy|mineralogist]], and member of the [[Parliament of Norway|Norwegian Parliament]], 1900–09.<ref name=gnis/><ref>{{cite web | url = https://geographic.org/geographic_names/name.php?uni=-2016940&fid=5991&c=south_georgia_and_the_south_sandwich_islands |title = Brøgger Glacier, Antarctica | website = Geographical Names | publisher = | accessdate = 21 January 2018}}</ref>

