{{Distinguish|List of free and open source software packages}} {{dynamic list}}
'''Freeware''' is [[software]] that is available for use at no monetary cost or for an optional fee,<ref>"[http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/freeware Freeware]" (2010). ''Merriam-Webster Online Dictionary''. Accessed January 13, 2010.</ref> but usually (although not necessarily) closed source with one or more restricted usage rights. [[Freeware]] is in contrast to [[commercial software]], which is typically sold for profit, but might be distributed for a business or commercial purpose in the aim to expand the [[marketshare]] of a "premium" product. Popular examples of [[closed-source]] freeware include [[Adobe Reader]], [[Free Studio]] and [[Skype]]. {{TOC right}}
